  + [authority_boundary] is planning_surface_not_signed_specification
  + [resolution] is [RefinedPhasePlan], [ManagerQueue], [RiskLedger], [ReadinessGate], or [Uncertainty]

  = must: preserve proof-backed readiness separately from intended capability
  = must: route Shaliach runtime before broader multi-agent concurrency
  = must: use completed SJS/DataDesign and narrative updates as inputs to Shaliach rather than rebuilding them immediately
  = must: keep local LLM serving and model inventory separate from core orchestration until runtime governance is stable
  - never: treat narrative updates as full narrative coverage recomputation
  - never: treat extracted ledgers as equivalent to deep Shaliach critique until S10 exists

& [DelineationPass] is the boundary protocol applied to this plan refinement
  @ [protocol] C:\Project\ReasoningFramework\platform\refinement\Delineation.sop
  + [field] is the user's request to revisit and refine the project plan after negotiated ledgers and narrative runtime updates
  + [subject] is the next useful plan for making NegotiatedCodingAgent long-turn ready
  + [inside] is reordering the active manager queue from current proof-backed readiness
  + [inside] is identifying the next governing implementation phase
  + [inside] is separating readiness gates from intended future capability
  + [inside] is preserving risks and unresolved items that affect long-turn cleanliness
  + [outside] is implementing Shaliach runtime in this planning checkpoint
  + [outside] is installing vLLM, Ollama models, WSL2, or Linux infrastructure in this planning checkpoint
  + [outside] is rewriting the original governing specification in this planning checkpoint
  + [references] is coordination/manager_job_notice.sop
  + [references] is coordination/project_narrative_surface.sop
  + [references] is coordination/framework_attention_load.sop
  + [references] is specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  + [uncertainty] is exact model-serving order may change after local inventory and Shaliach governance are proven

  = must: preserve inside, outside, references, and uncertainty as separate legs
  = must: keep implementation slices bounded by the current subject
  = must: re-run delineation when a future user request changes the active subject from planning to implementation or infrastructure
  - never: absorb adjacent attractive work into the active slice merely because it is nearby

& [PlanShift] is what changed after the latest work
  + [previous_plan_shape] is build durable rails first, then fill missing SOP subsystems
  + [new_plan_shape] is make existing rails govern agent execution, then add multi-agent coordination and model-hosting depth
  + [completed_enabler] is S08_runtime_conversation_kernel
  + [completed_enabler] is S09_protocol_registry
  + [completed_enabler] is S11_negotiated_sjs_datadesign_ledgers
  + [completed_enabler] is S12_project_narrative_surface_seed_and_runtime_update
  + [result] is Shaliach can now be designed against real runtime artifacts: protocol activations, negotiated ledgers, manager reviews, programmer reports, conversation surface, and narrative updates

& [RefinedPhasePlan] is the staged path from current readiness to stronger long-turn autonomy
  + [Phase1] is ShaliachRuntimeCore completed
  + [Phase2] is OrchestratorGovernanceIntegration
  + [Phase3] is WorkProductTraceability
  + [Phase4] is MultiConversationCoordination
  + [Phase5] is LocalModelServingAndDiversity
  + [Phase6] is LongRunHarnessAndRecovery

& [Phase1 ShaliachRuntimeCore] is the next governing implementation phase
  + [primary_slice] is S10_shaliach_faculty_runtime
  + [phase_status] is completed
  + [objective] is implement Shaliach higher/lower reasoning with selected faculty and internal-perspective passes
  + [input_surface] is negotiated LayerPackage ledgers
  + [input_surface] is ProtocolActivationSet
  + [input_surface] is ManagerReview
  + [input_surface] is ProgrammerReport
  + [input_surface] is ConversationSurfaceFile
  + [output_surface] is ShaliachFinding
  + [output_surface] is ShaliachResponseCoordination
  + [required_actions] is advisory_note, warning, pause_signal, request_rework, no_finding
  + [proof_route] is tests for severity selection, targeted artifact repair instructions, no-finding behavior, and pause/rework escalation
  + [readiness_gate] is Shaliach can inspect negotiated ledgers and block or warn before Manager approval or implementation review
  + [completion_proof] is tests passed with 20 tests and dry-run wrote ShaliachFinding records in runs/20260529T113710Z

& [Phase2 OrchestratorGovernanceIntegration] is the phase that makes the rails active during runs
  + [objective] is emit protocol activation artifacts, Shaliach findings, conversation proof updates, and narrative updates as normal run events
  + [work_slice] is integrate ProtocolRegistry output into run_root
  + [work_slice] is attach Shaliach findings to layer packages before Manager gate
  + [work_slice] is update active conversation surface at run start, layer approval, implementation write, and run completion
  + [work_slice] is update narrative with structured run events beyond a single completion block
  + [proof_route] is dry-run emits protocol_activation.sop, shaliach findings, updated package ledgers, and narrative run events

& [Phase3 WorkProductTraceability] is the phase that answers why each file changed
  + [primary_slice] is S14_file_change_surface
  + [objective] is add solution_uuid records and file-to-solution index entries for implementation slices
  + [input_surface] is WorkSlice
  + [input_surface] is ProgrammerReport
  + [input_surface] is ManagerReview
  + [input_surface] is changed file list
  + [output_surface] is FileChangeSurface
  + [proof_route] is file path resolves to solution_uuid, justification_ref, proof_ref, and commit_ref when available

& [Phase4 MultiConversationCoordination] is the phase for multiple active threads
  + [primary_slice] is S13_mailbox_and_notice_coordination
  + [objective] is implement inbox, notice, read_cursor, coordination claim, conflict signal, and rendezvous packets
  + [dependency] is ShaliachRuntimeCore should exist first so coordination warnings have protocol teeth
  + [proof_route] is two simulated conversation surfaces exchange boundary offer, acknowledgement, and rendezvous packet without deleting mailbox history

& [Phase5 LocalModelServingAndDiversity] is the phase for real model swarm hosting
  + [objective] is verify local model inventory and decide Ollama versus vLLM route from actual machine constraints
  + [preferred_hardware_path] is WSL2 or Linux vLLM for RTX 5090 throughput when disk and setup constraints are acceptable
  + [fallback_path] is Ollama or OpenAI-compatible server for simpler local operation
  + [proof_route] is model health check, concurrent request test, role-to-model routing test, and dry-run/live-run comparison
  + [risk] is spending setup effort before orchestration governance can use model diversity well

& [Phase6 LongRunHarnessAndRecovery] is the phase that makes overnight work operational
  + [objective] is run a bounded long-turn job with periodic surface updates, proof checkpoints, and reentry validation
  + [input_surface] is manager_job_notice
  + [input_surface] is project_narrative_surface
  + [input_surface] is conversation_surface
  + [operator] is load rails, take next ready slice, implement, test, update ledgers, commit, push, repeat until blocker or budget
  + [proof_route] is interrupted/reentered run resumes from conversation_uuid and narrative frontier without losing completed proof or dirty-worktree attribution

