& [RiskLedger] is the current plan risk surface
  + [risk] is Shaliach runtime could become ceremonial if it activates every faculty for every event
  + [mitigation] is select perspectives by artifact and severity; default to no_finding for clean low-risk events
  + [risk] is extracted ledgers may overfit keyword lines from weak model proposals
  + [mitigation] is Shaliach should grade ledger support and request rework when evidence is too thin
  + [risk] is narrative append-only updates can drift from coverage truth
  + [mitigation] is future narrative runtime must recompute coverage and stale status, not only append summaries
  + [risk] is local model setup can consume time before the agent loop is ready to use model diversity
  + [mitigation] is defer vLLM/Ollama inventory work until Shaliach and orchestration governance can exploit diversity

& [ReadinessGate] is the minimum condition before claiming stronger long-turn readiness
  + [required] is Shaliach runtime emits findings from protocol activations and negotiated ledgers
  + [required] is orchestrator writes Shaliach findings and protocol activation artifacts into run output
  + [required] is active conversation surface updates during run lifecycle, not only at completion
  + [required] is tests cover warning, pause/rework, and no-finding paths
  + [required] is one dry-run proves run output, conversation surface, and narrative surface stay coherent

  = must: claim long-turn readiness only with proof for the gate conditions
